 Martin O'Malley's cover of Taylor Swift's "Bad Blood" on The View this morning raises a ton of questions: Can O'Malley hear the sound of his own voice? Has he lived in the 30 Rock "Bubble" his whole life, where he's so attractive that no one has told him that he can't sing? Is he off on the timing of the song, or is one of The View hosts just way overly eager and sings too early? Is this better or worse than his Green Day cover ?
